#include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
	int T;
	scanf("%d", &T);

	for (int t = 0; t < T; t++)
	{
		int A[9][9];
		int R[9],C[9],B[9];
		for (int i = 0; i < 9; i++)
			R[i]=C[i]=B[i]=0;
		for (int i = 0; i < 9; i++)
			for (int j = 0; j < 9; j++)
			{
				int x;
				scanf("%d", &x);
				x=x-1;
				A[i][j] = x;
				R[i] |= (1 << x);
				C[i] |= (1 << x);
				B[i/3+3*(j/3)] |= (1 << x); 
			}

		bool ok = true;
		for (int i = 0; i < 9; i++)
		{
			if (R[i] != 511 || B[i] != 511 || C[i] != 511  )
			{
				ok = false;
				break;
			}
		}

		if (ok)
			printf("Its A Sudoku\n");
		else
			printf("Not A Sudoku\n");
	}	

	return 0;
}
